            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-003-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 3:2 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 4:1, 6:1, etc. for similar cases. We reconstruct
                            this verse here on the basis of ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not
                            omitted, see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >וַיַּעַן אִיֹּוב וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘And Job answered and said’ (Job 3:2). | C: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov da
                                ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>Da baslady Ijov da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>Da bašlady Ijov da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-003-fn2" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: Mist likely a
                            mistranslation. | C: <emph>tizlär</emph>. | QB: <emph>tizlär</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>tizler</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>tizler</emph>. | BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">בִרְכָּיִם </foreign>
                            ‘knees’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-003-fn3" type="footnote">Spelled <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">ײֵמֵישֵיא</foreign>
                            ; perhaps a hypercorrect form of <emph>jemese</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
